<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="3.[177,1381,261,525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[177,529,294,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Reassessment of the Cyprus Spiny Mouse would probably result in classification as Endangered because of its small fragmented populations and human pressure on the island. It also competes with introduced Roof Rats (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[710,885,412,446]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Rattus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="600" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rattus">Rattus rattus</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="600" type="bibRefCitation_list">
<paragraph blockId="3.[177,1381,261,525]" pageId="3" pageNumber="600">
